skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "890ce689-82bd-4b08-9abb-13d9887bb380", "value": "An engine in which the oscillating motion of the beam is translated via gearing to a rotative motion."}
{"id": "f7dc8070-41c9-4431-bc8b-5539b893670a", "value": "A small self-contained rotative Beam Steam Engine."}
{"id": "9a3fc5d6-19cd-4449-b755-593f3b0bfac0", "value": "A rotative beam steam engine patented in 1790."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "c9248cfe-cc24-4f53-ab9c-85cac73cc7b1", "value": "FISH Components Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "6fdce181-d41c-41b7-b9e7-6061b92644fa", "value": "Used to record the constituent elements of a building or monument."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "3da68bfe-8206-4c3c-8322-df8d2ff99c74", "value": "Originally a room in a house where a family would gather, usually in the evening, to sit and read, write, sew, play music etc. This term has become commonly used as an alternative to living room."}
{"id": "89390dd5-97ed-4443-9104-fe396ffba20a", "value": "A room for general daily use, usually in a family dwelling."}
{"id": "866a1fa1-9ae7-4c82-9189-9ce118bd0dd3", "value": "A sitting room or lounge in a house intended mainly for use during the morning."}

{"id": "769ef156-9387-45ef-99d3-7adee9c6fa6e", "value": "A projecting spout to throw water from a gutter away from the wall, frequently decorated with grotesque figures to spew out evil away from the House of God."}

{"id": "4b4b2e61-0f3b-4ff9-918a-4a00114cfaf8", "value": "A small timber fixed to a wall to support items such as cladding. Also a strip of timber fixed across two or more parallel boards to join them together or conceal their join."}
{"id": "88176625-add8-4c12-b42e-77e1f799f828", "value": "A rib which spans a vault passing from springer to springer at right angles to the axis of the vault."}

{"id": "50771baa-245d-4042-8205-9c9f14fd6f93", "value": "The junction of two timbers at right angles, with chamfers or mouldings meeting on a diagonal line, where one timber is cut to fit around the chamfer or moulding of the other timber."}
{"id": "44a4cea5-7f42-4f14-803f-685bb1a69f0e", "value": "A screen separating the choir from other parts of the church."}
{"id": "bd58e3b2-8791-4bdc-955d-e06aee380cb3", "value": "A room where the public can sit, often in hotels and airports."}
{"id": "9b4b152e-d177-4faf-af65-4ac478a70765", "value": "The area at the end of an axle or shaft around which a wheel, bearing etc. pivots or rotates."}
{"id": "128a98ed-22bc-4dff-bd4a-0bd4f5c4dcc8", "value": "A room in which commercial or administrative activities are carried out."}
{"id": "cafb3f63-b7a3-43a0-aef4-f8083dacd35b", "value": "A prime mover which is rotated by the reaction from forcing a moving fluid to change direction."}
{"id": "80b27642-e05b-4c35-9571-ce3f0e4a97ba", "value": "A meeting room intended specifically for the use of a board of directors or governors of an organization or company.."}
{"id": "de129905-49b1-46c2-815d-68cbbc79120b", "value": "A signal usually mounted on a gantry, be it mechanical or electronic, to provide guidance to traindrivers on access to sections of track."}
{"id": "0103f580-ea3e-42b3-96ba-dec19515dbb0", "value": "A roof, circular in plan, usually semicircular in section, over a circular, square or polygonal base."}
{"id": "fb66c805-4ed8-4ec6-8a1b-01bddcf50ef0", "value": "A power driven cloth-weaving machine."}

{"id": "7516f859-4fb2-48d5-b7f7-e694f57775c6", "value": "A piece of stone or timber with a small cup shaped depression in its upper surface, set into the ground to fasten a door, gate, window etc to allow it to open and shut."}
{"id": "6ab953ba-ab72-44e1-a39c-27ef2720d1e4", "value": "A junction whereby two members or elements of an artificial structure or mechanism are joined or fitted together, whether rigidly or hinged."}
{"id": "ebacef39-23ff-4bfd-b209-203745f82f43", "value": "An item used to fasten, bind or join one item to another."}
{"id": "6270341c-91f1-40af-88c9-2a4473181650", "value": "An inclined timber used to support and provide rigidity to roofs, partitions etc."}
{"id": "8ba9e6d9-9f67-424e-9320-9c66ad790347", "value": "A piece of wood of square or rectangular section driven through a scarf joint to tighten it"}
{"id": "7c8bd6dd-7fae-4bb2-a414-420e47bb0004", "value": "A metal binding or ring fastened around the top of a pile to stop splitting."}

{"id": "fea35ee5-cf7b-45e2-a0de-8dbbc14728a5", "value": "A movable joint, usually consisting of two plates joined by a pin, that fastens a door, gate, window etc. to its frame and allows it to open and shut."}
{"id": "ae47932e-d157-49c2-965e-acc3a01bd24b", "value": "The framing of a door or window with two columns piers or pilasters which support a lintel,entablature etc."}
{"id": "5ed5a201-effa-4aed-8372-42d471b0700a", "value": "A small hinged opening within a large door."}
{"id": "f13b7004-32c7-4b60-8bc4-8a56ecc47cee", "value": "A door divided horizontally into two parts, independently hinged."}
{"id": "583929a8-352b-4fcc-9339-2466ffe2eac4", "value": "A planked or battened door, with large nails or pegs with projecting heads keeping it intact."}
{"id": "5712903a-137c-4239-9bb7-a5a0f7fab49a", "value": "A door adorned with panels, usually arranged in pairs."}
{"id": "0fac804a-2025-4e5b-b6eb-c6abcb98ec6c", "value": "The wood, stone or brick framework, lining a doorway, from which the door is hung."}
{"id": "961ba834-a9a1-4f05-8273-2c807bb0fa4c", "value": "A wooden bar sliding from a long channel at one side of a doorway into a socket in the other jamb so as to bar the door."}
{"id": "8472c003-faa2-40e8-bb5c-5c784e22c8e1", "value": "A door made up of vertical planks on the outer face and horizontal planks on the inner face."}
{"id": "52184dc1-590a-40ce-9027-197a0b00cf12", "value": "The entrance to a building, apartment or any enclosure consisting of a movable barrier, usually lockable, of wood or other materials."}
{"id": "48c7efa3-d1a2-4e41-8de0-3d556608b41b", "value": "The space in which a door is placed, allowing passage through."}
{"id": "0684f8c7-9c4e-4e6c-be92-66de0b8fd4d8", "value": "A horizontal door within, and usually flush with surface of, a floor, ceiling or roof."}
{"id": "d64f4fe0-cf4f-49f4-9114-089ea2f60b68", "value": "A priest's private entrance into a church, usually found on the south side of the chancel."}
{"id": "38fdb175-efd5-4726-80a6-c73f82431ec1", "value": "A door with a planked outer face and spaced horizontal members such as battens or ledges on the inner face."}
{"id": "cdd4b3ab-2a67-4157-bf9d-5ac853c41052", "value": "An internal door flush with, and decorated to match, the wall it is set in for the purpose of concealment."}
{"id": "3006f751-3a19-4862-8355-eb8357d194a2", "value": "A semi-circular window, often decorated and with its glazing bars radiating like the ribs of an opened fan, set above a door."}

{"id": "babea93f-68cf-44f8-9f66-662f5e6e7218", "value": "An early power loom in which the shedding actions of the machine were controlled by tappets, or wipers, which received their motion from a rotating cam shaft positioned at one side of the loom."}
{"id": "63917d88-addd-487f-9a27-8b81637be4e4", "value": "A collective term embracing a church tower's entire structure, including its spire."}
{"id": "71430512-fef8-438b-be27-045d9741e369", "value": "A steeple in which the spire resembles a crown."}
{"id": "61af4c34-a400-4918-ad91-49e127dc2e31", "value": "A plan in which the front entrance opens into a lobby opposite to an axial chimney stack."}
{"id": "df42b365-c054-4d00-92c3-4ff34c13549f", "value": "A plan featuring a doorless entry to a lobby in front of an axial chimney-stack."}
{"id": "b9afadd6-b704-4598-a3e0-b8b4f697de3b", "value": "The principal storey of a building, containing the main reception rooms, when not situated on ground level."}

{"id": "5d7757f4-d3f1-4280-b0f4-d8da2c0664c4", "value": "A steam engine in which the spent steam leaving the cylinder passes to a condenser instead of being exhausted to the atmosphere. The condenser creates a partial vacuum which increases the pressure drop across the engine, so raising its efficiency."}

{"id": "417802ca-8176-44bc-8624-392ffff5452c", "value": "Machines for automatically feeding fuel onto the fire of steam boilers and other furnace plant, introduced at the beginning of the 19th century."}
{"id": "066a123b-eefc-4d58-94c4-8be45a377c51", "value": "A hand operated machine for winding cotton and linen thread into balls - invented in 1802."}
{"id": "2e139b4d-21df-473c-8c14-077e760e3234", "value": "A wheeled device supporting a windmill's fantail that moves around a trackway thus turning the windmill into the wind."}

{"id": "1955878b-fabd-4c30-9c74-68f929cb67c8", "value": "A bladed wheel attached to the rear, and at right angles to the main sails, of a windmill. Connected to winding gear, the fantail would catch the wind when it changed direction, allowing the mill to move automatically into the wind."}
{"id": "d1a83601-be4a-4d81-9dbe-52f6112943ce", "value": "A surface made up of small pieces of hard material such as stone or tile, often in a decorative pattern."}
{"id": "7cb6ef56-2d51-4600-933c-b5a0e9a6b2c5", "value": "The lower, horizontal surface of a room on which people walk. Can also mean a storey of a building."}
{"id": "09740fbb-4333-4322-a715-2244c718d2f7", "value": "A dining hall for the use of seasonal labourers."}
{"id": "221fb1db-5856-4e67-98bc-9f4be41a1347", "value": "A room where meals, particularly breakfast are partaken."}
{"id": "ddd11861-d716-42b8-b37c-0fa33fe2c640", "value": "A hall normally reserved for holding feasts on special occasions."}
{"id": "65d82f5f-0cf2-472c-8c7a-fca82cce9d7e", "value": "A room, furnished with tables and chairs, where meals and refreshments are served and consumed."}
{"id": "abb9a80f-e159-48e6-bc2a-2d20aca271fd", "value": "A room intended for the taking of refreshments, usually containing a counter from which they are served."}
{"id": "4b16b62c-5886-40d2-839b-66f91b1795ed", "value": "A dining hall, usually in a monastery or college."}
{"id": "efc91472-4dc9-4c03-9f06-f381156beb57", "value": "A combination of timbers to form a frame placed at intervals and carrying the purlins."}
{"id": "5a25af0d-a302-4694-abae-e4441f29baa8", "value": "A truss with braces crossing and fixed to each other, thus tying a pair of rafters together."}

{"id": "f98f6be4-f476-470b-b03a-28a5e038e615", "value": "A truss with transverse timbers, like a tie-beam from which the middle section has been removed, supported on braces and carrying hammer-posts and braces that carry the open structure of the roof."}
{"id": "c0d2ee39-a229-4078-86c3-ce81cef012a0", "value": "A truss with a transverse timber like a hammer-beam, but braced to a principal or collar without a hammer-post."}
{"id": "a0b6d4ed-9cb4-4864-89f8-f5db2ac234f4", "value": "A truss in which spaces between timbers are filled, as between rooms and at the ends of a building."}
{"id": "a272b659-453e-47b2-8e2f-2682e73f0b9a", "value": "A roof truss supported by arcade posts in an aisled building."}
{"id": "1ea04f35-8c73-4fac-91a2-a4c750b702d8", "value": "A truss of slighter construction between principal trusses in an elaborate roof."}
{"id": "6c12d63d-f00a-4bae-8b8d-6bff82fcea1f", "value": "A roof truss used for small spans with a saw-tooth overall shape braced by vertical and diagonal members."}
{"id": "ace839ca-88d0-4266-8123-9b84c803ba6e", "value": "The structure across the lower end of a medieval hall containing the spere, its supporting posts and tie-beam."}
{"id": "0674e4e3-dc6b-481c-9bad-56e2b0bedab2", "value": "A pair of principal rafters with a tiebeam, usually with a collar."}
{"id": "ab2ce53d-be12-4e46-bebd-c3784bf031ef", "value": "An arched, or bow-shaped, segmental timber truss with its ends tied together by a straight or cambered member."}

{"id": "13f6204e-408e-4acd-b42d-94dddf86609b", "value": "A pair of timbers, or blades, usually curved, rising from a place at or near ground level to a point at or near the apex of a roof, forming an approximately triangular frame on which the subsidiary structure rests."}
{"id": "e5c95404-9ba8-426e-9f66-251c454a2db1", "value": "A truss comprising principal rafters and wall-posts secured by knee-braces or sling-braces, but lacking tiebeams."}

{"id": "ba599b34-6356-4c74-a87f-28e1d56e1161", "value": "A truss with two curved kerb-principals, which are the short principal rafters rising froma tiebeam to a collar, placed either side of a crown strut."}
{"id": "639aba1a-0191-49a5-b813-f9626a3ce1b8", "value": "A complete cross-frame from ground level to ridge in a box-framed building."}
{"id": "c35b8a89-f0fd-464f-9421-b54ed9d11668", "value": "A truss which does not subdivide a space, as in the centre of a hall of two bays or in an undivided building such as a barn."}
{"id": "43eeaf6a-3076-4421-8495-66ba85c646aa", "value": "A truss with paired vertical posts set on the tie-beam and supporting collar purlins or plates."}
{"id": "2e5b49a8-b8e3-4b5b-99ca-9bcdc250db7a", "value": "A pair of common rafters with a collar."}
{"id": "3fd3bed2-1bf5-425e-b230-14e6fefa0807", "value": "A truss in which two pairs of arch braces form a continuous curve from the wall-heads or below to meet in the centre of the collar."}
{"id": "de806f35-3e50-4bd2-99d1-1e6deb237600", "value": "A flat, horizontal strip, block or moulding, sometimes decorated, on a facade or interrupting an architectural feature such as a column."}
{"id": "e88357cc-53b3-418a-85db-8cce5c9046a7", "value": "A recess, often containing shelves and usually fitted with a door or doors, used for the storage of items."}
{"id": "a2a35abb-6a54-4a7d-8af8-96fd0d20daab", "value": "A substantial vertical member, usually a component of a main framework."}

{"id": "b999df6d-6c73-48f5-bfeb-88bf97bdae10", "value": "A casement, usually wooden, in a mill enclosing the grindstones and preventing the loss of ground material before it is channelled into sacks."}
{"id": "629df0cc-88fd-48f9-86f8-4d108a365c2c", "value": "The large main axle on which a waterwheel, which turns the shaft, and a pitwheel are mounted."}
{"id": "4f64eebb-e92e-4a35-84af-1ba916c9eaa3", "value": "A gulley in the form of a circle for holding vertical posts in the walls of iron age round houses."}
{"id": "9b60281c-86a9-4fe5-8136-08a83626818e", "value": "A housing, normally of triangular section, in a post to take the end of a prop, to hold the post upright during construction."}
{"id": "1475d8ab-13c2-432a-a5db-ae5bb278097a", "value": "The main gear wheel, which is engaged by a brake to halt or slow the machinery, mounted on the windshaft of a windmill."}

{"id": "4054fa99-83b1-4fda-9ec8-0dc82292c932", "value": "The upper parts of walls carried on arcades or colonnades in the nave, choir or transepts of a church or hall, rising higher than the lean-to roofs of the aisles and pierced with windows to allow light to penetrate."}
{"id": "d06bc47c-a5d7-4510-a2ef-9aa92f51e62b", "value": "A wooden, metal or stone strip attached to the floor between the door posts in a doorway covering the joint between two floor surfaces."}
{"id": "407b6502-2928-4f5c-8bf6-0c172179317b", "value": "An iron bar or rod running through the core of a windmill's windshaft that causes the opening and shutting of the vanes on patent sails."}
{"id": "01ab6ad8-3804-4d29-bfa3-91dff3529cec", "value": "The lowest part of a structure, such as a pier, or the section of an order on which the shaft of a column sits."}
{"id": "3562e0b4-98db-4b7f-838c-79ce20198f71", "value": "A general term given to all horizontal timbers laid on walls or posts in order to support other timbers."}
{"id": "0a99c30a-99e0-441a-ba4d-554e12ce453d", "value": "A straight brace from rafter to collar in a common rafter truss."}
{"id": "ffec6955-3c8c-4486-820c-7a6506eccee8", "value": "The large wooden framework that supports the grinding wheels in a corn mill."}
{"id": "aa024611-0f52-49f1-912a-6b099754bcb9", "value": "A wooden nail, round or square in section, used to fix a joint."}
{"id": "677546a4-c129-462e-9fd1-b2998a695b26", "value": "A stone or brick used on a corner to reinforce it and also as decoration."}

{"id": "da0e33d2-3f6a-4dc9-8069-2fb3350adf09", "value": "A four-armed metal coupling, positioned at the centre of a windmill's sails, connected to the front of the striking rod and the shutter bars of all the sails, causing the shutters to open and close."}
{"id": "f592908f-664c-4b91-93ab-cbe846ea2cb8", "value": "A shaped or decorated raised panel below the sill of a window or a niche."}
{"id": "65256178-d9c1-45a6-a79e-7fb3357115a0", "value": "A flat, horizontal piece of timber or masonry projecting from or recessed into a wall to hold objects."}

{"id": "06cfd528-c912-43d1-a6d9-c7ec4f5c5259", "value": "A metallic rod attached to a high point on a building and leading to the earth for the purpose of conducting lightning away from the main body of the building."}
{"id": "de914ef3-b84e-4776-902c-93689fbe325a", "value": "A channel, usually placed upstream of a mill, that carries water from a river or other water source to a waterwheel."}

{"id": "50c69675-6f94-4315-a3da-f1893f01be17", "value": "The side compartment of a building, usually a church, hall or barn, separated from the main body of the building by an arcade; or a passage allowing access to rows of seats in an auditorium or church."}
{"id": "a7f4096d-9175-45b1-9fb5-9a842cd0c218", "value": "A vertical iron bar fixed within a window opening to support a leaded light."}
{"id": "63a40e9c-707b-41ff-9f6c-447175d20a5a", "value": "A section of stone or brickwork employed in a timber-framed building to fill the spaces between uprights or studs."}

{"id": "a1701d6e-cd2e-498c-8ab2-0917b223096c", "value": "A funnel, connected to an opening in the floor of the tun encasing the grindstones in a corn mill, that carries ground meal away to a bin or sack."}
{"id": "4afe3fa2-1059-4bd4-8b23-abd39ac29f53", "value": "A horizontal member supporting the posts in a timber framed structure."}
{"id": "9bafb7dc-5d04-4bee-a461-58b3c014f28c", "value": "A flattened rectangular version of a column of one of the classical orders."}

{"id": "7cb2ea28-e89b-4af5-ad82-b796f971802d", "value": "A panel of often decorated wrought-ironwork forming the arch between two gate-piers or standards or above a gate. Also used for an arched support for a lamp-holder between two standards."}
{"id": "9d0b7b7c-4fb7-43e4-acc7-f2c843d9dc5e", "value": "The main gearwheel in a water mill, sharing the same shaft as the exterior waterwheel but placed within the mill."}
{"id": "7524d351-418e-42ac-8030-35f4ef3431ae", "value": "An opening in a structure which is arched."}
{"id": "219034c4-0737-4801-ba1c-1b2ea7e5c1a7", "value": "A horizontal member of a wall frame between posts or studs, also the horizontal member in panelling, a panelled door or a window."}
{"id": "b664c252-a642-4fff-bdd7-28dad8063acd", "value": "A rectangular recess along the edge of a timber to receive a shutter, door or window."}
{"id": "14af1d95-c573-4d6f-9ffa-a9fdd9f3b920", "value": "The main axle projecting through the front of a windmill on which the sails are mounted."}
{"id": "49b6d9f3-f32c-48e6-b36d-0658d10e870d", "value": "A part of a building or structure that is an element of the construction."}

{"id": "03e98bd3-5ec6-497b-8988-84f2ec253180", "value": "An opening in a wall that is usually narrow on the outside but widens internally to allow a defender to stand and shoot through the loophole."}
{"id": "40b73cb8-b0eb-4c8a-ac2d-979e9b36e3c1", "value": "A metal or stone plate or tablet, usually inscribed, set into a wall, pedestal, floor etc., often serving as a memorial."}
{"id": "59f6a1f9-06e4-424a-b891-56eef2327a64", "value": "A horizontal member connecting rafters or cruck blades at a point between their feet and the apex of the roof."}
{"id": "ae90d012-31a2-4e31-bcd1-5e95f5d91bba", "value": "A pedestrian passageway, often elevated, connecting two buildings or sections within a building."}
{"id": "49be88ff-03db-44f8-a31d-ca8d5cc5f154", "value": "A small projection designed to allow space for a bed."}
{"id": "f1d5e417-9d09-4005-bdc5-8c4b7e35a6ab", "value": "The ridge formed at the intersection of two vaulted surfaces."}
{"id": "258ef43d-8331-4e5a-a79d-7a88841e307c", "value": "Short vertical timbers which go from the rafters to the inner plate on a thick wall."}
{"id": "0061052e-8179-4166-84fb-f1201b432a1b", "value": "A stone ring built to enclose and sometimes revet a burial mound or cairn."}
{"id": "61aff949-9de0-4dd2-81f0-d320d2d03c69", "value": "A framed fireplace hood built on a bressumer and extending from one outer wall to the other or to a spere."}
{"id": "da6a9860-f7bd-4094-ac96-795ee653a126", "value": "A shallow, ornamental recess, often arched and semicircular in plan, set in a wall or pier and usually containing a statue or ornament."}

{"id": "d958b936-f260-43f0-a94c-855d1986e7e0", "value": "A short, tapered, vertical stone supporting a rough stone disc so resembling a toadstool, often forming one of several uprights on which a timber structure, such as a granary rests, protecting the building from damp and vermin."}
{"id": "4bb06d10-b2af-4651-80fa-569b6cb18747", "value": "The rotating top section of a tower or smock mill."}
{"id": "7569e739-a4f4-4a4f-854b-be7a456e0bfb", "value": "A small support designed to help support a weight, such as that of a projecting member."}

{"id": "4ebc2de7-9f2e-4de1-a0b9-4a3e9b5d805e", "value": "A decorative piece descending vertically from the bottom of a newel on a staircase, or from the junction of barge boards at the apex of a gable."}
{"id": "548d3f44-677a-45f8-9de6-35ed8cc111fb", "value": "The opening at the base of a chimney stack."}
{"id": "c92425cf-dc3e-46cd-9ad1-a757f41c2cdf", "value": "A large stone laid horizontally to form the roof of a chamber."}
{"id": "c323dbd5-1612-4448-9783-532070ae70a7", "value": "A projecting, sometimes decorated, finish to a moulding, chamfer, label, hood-mould or string-course."}
{"id": "593d184c-537b-4613-ae85-c17f9ead4e46", "value": "Any member that connects two bodies, such as the sloping sides of a roof, to prevent them pulling apart."}
{"id": "1a6effa7-0c82-40eb-b188-1cea8a9ea72a", "value": "The principal longitudinal member or spine of a windmill sail, extending from the stock and supporting the sailbars."}
{"id": "552ae0d2-d524-4d79-a9d6-3d204b4426c7", "value": "A usually shallow cut linear feature often used for drainage."}
{"id": "4d97d2e9-6f08-4988-831d-c1709193a70d", "value": "A canopy suspended, or on pillars, over a throne or altar."}
{"id": "27558838-cee9-4f18-b386-5693aecd8508", "value": "The external face or elevation of a building, especially the principal front."}
{"id": "35e909b4-11b3-4a02-bf9a-99cd05fe7dd6", "value": "The point or block from which an arch or vault starts. The block generally has a horizontal base and sloped top."}
{"id": "b1401e42-dcb8-49a4-b4ef-04d4aa43647d", "value": "A polygonal or semicircular recess projecting from an external wall, often with a rounded vault."}
{"id": "adcafbe2-614f-40da-ba38-ce3031df39aa", "value": "A vertical timber in a truss, descending from the ridge, and projecting below the lower transverse timber, normally used with scissor beams."}
{"id": "90b14264-ed1e-48ff-bb48-d6d9aa9d6362", "value": "The main vertical beam standing at the centre of a post mill carrying the bearing upon which the body of the mill rotates."}
{"id": "ad84bb86-5ff3-4f3c-b264-655e3bf0bea6", "value": "The area directly in front of a fireplace or the floor of a firecplace itself."}

{"id": "f20ed79f-d44a-4b7e-888a-beec5765b223", "value": "A large approximately triangular stone at the foot of a gable, cut to have a horizontal bed and a top conforming, wholly or in part, to the slope of the gable."}
{"id": "d2302716-8a1f-4ba5-9237-9eb91a9610de", "value": "A pole projecting to the rear of a post mill to allow the sails to be moved into the wind."}
{"id": "2274f624-4c75-48d1-b78c-22097b686445", "value": "A mechanism within a windmill, attached to the striking rod, allowing the opening and closing of the shutters or vanes of patent sails."}
{"id": "7a5d07c6-2328-42a4-93f4-ef8e62766750", "value": "A short timber linking two pieces of timber."}
{"id": "208a0157-ca1a-4b8a-a257-188467c94ab8", "value": "A framed canopy suspended above the dais or high table at the upper end of a hall."}
{"id": "157ba921-7879-46f3-b121-10ba13281c52", "value": "A raised platform, especially in a theatre or auditorium, for the use of performers or speakers etc."}
{"id": "99859e22-320e-4102-8372-1613d2784731", "value": "An H-sectioned strip of lead used to hold panes of glass in position in stained-glass windows or other leaded lights."}
{"id": "66959f1d-0642-4cde-9094-a7d509435ee0", "value": "The vertical lining of a doorway, window or other opening."}
{"id": "c0387a16-802c-4272-b436-5d62e9e4faaa", "value": "Horizontal timbers laid parallel to each other on which flooring is laid and to which a ceiling is fixed."}
{"id": "41a61c43-43a2-4562-9042-bf4896f1681f", "value": "A cantilevered block projecting from the face of a wall and supporting a structure such as a parapet, beam or arch."}
{"id": "2954bd05-0381-40ee-987a-cfc04f24d97d", "value": "A room or space with an arched ceiling or roof, the depth of which exceeds its span."}
{"id": "c695c0a9-ec5f-4484-ba65-f12997eb275a", "value": "A protective covering applied to the top of a wall, chimney, gable etc., usually curved, sloping or ridged to prevent rainwater settling."}

{"id": "fce8a70c-8c52-43d8-b69f-d3d88bb40005", "value": "A framework of crossed or parallel wooden or metal bars placed over an opening to prevent access but allow the passage of air, light, water etc."}
{"id": "8689c69f-e766-4a3a-9bd6-d1a01a44b1aa", "value": "A board fixed at the gable end to purlins, often decorated."}

{"id": "1117da4a-b515-4459-8268-3d2e0882171a", "value": "The quasi-triangular area between, and defined by, the upper sections of a pair of adjacent arches, or between the curve of an arch and the angle of a surrounding frame or structure."}

{"id": "eeea24bc-6f14-4d45-825a-b2b044859230", "value": "The first driven gearwheel on the vertical shaft within a corn mill which meshes with the brake wheel in a windmill, or the pit wheel in a watermill."}
{"id": "a600e8d6-e59a-4d1f-adb5-860d41277d21", "value": "Two intersecting beams set on the ground to support a post, usually for a post mill."}
{"id": "7e5dd75e-75ea-45b8-ba5d-3b39817c3275", "value": "A flat, circular stone, usually made of sandstone, used in pairs for grinding corn and other meal."}

{"id": "22e9caad-6b9f-4acf-8a19-f5818c0e7d4d", "value": "The impost, or point at which a vault rests upon its support, and from which it seems to spring. Hence the term describes the bottom stone of a vault, which lies on the impost."}
{"id": "ee5077a6-8b5d-4f11-bc82-b0a6bc24511c", "value": "A diagonal brace running from an end of a cross tree to the vertical post to support this."}
{"id": "f58eda37-aa53-4df8-aac9-11ab24783bc3", "value": "A subsidiary member, usually vertical, in a framed wall or partition."}
{"id": "de1e71ac-8273-4f8e-b446-0360ba3ec2dd", "value": "A horizontal iron bar set in a window opening to which a leaded light is fixed."}
{"id": "2a3eb689-3dca-49e7-817c-4808da64613c", "value": "A structure, part of a structure or area consisting of plain masonry."}

{"id": "61c40072-d574-4087-a7db-7eb98c680847", "value": "A cutting, bank or block positioned against the wall of a trench, fort, parapet etc. to allow riflemen to shoot over the crest of the wall or parapet from a standing position."}
{"id": "6e48c801-3dea-4d3c-88c4-4f5a44d4db0b", "value": "A type of foundation in the form of a post sunk into the ground to support a building platform."}

{"id": "fd9daf4c-1a4a-4854-abda-e6a979678c3a", "value": "A curved construction, spanning an opening, formed from wedge-shaped blocks supported by mutual pressure; they can also be formed from moulded concrete and cast metal."}
{"id": "fa9ec6d5-c5e1-4b8d-a5bd-ad90211fd9a0", "value": "A raised platform at the end of a hall on which the high table sat, though sometimes used to describe the table itself."}
{"id": "92c3b080-5301-4591-916b-7bc5e7b092ec", "value": "A member whose purpose is to keep two other members apart, so acting in a state of compression."}
{"id": "bf7b871c-763c-44e4-839f-6c1b2ec455f7", "value": "A wall, usually perforated to allow free passage of air, supporting the ground-floor joists of a building."}
{"id": "ab8d1e1b-e342-4752-a621-d988060b4503", "value": "An area or series of tiles applied, usually to an interior floor or wall's surface, for practical or decorative effect."}
{"id": "b96625ac-c955-4826-ac3c-85ba66a7283c", "value": "An opening in a wall, roof, door, etc to allow light to enter. Usually used to include all component parts."}
{"id": "544baba3-b644-43d0-8d11-19cc09738402", "value": "A hinged, sliding or rolling door placed over a window's exterior or interior."}
{"id": "dcf4cd32-ff93-451d-8322-180267766d62", "value": "The lowest part, or base, of a structure, sometimes built into the ground, on which the weight of the whole rests."}
{"id": "4b779c24-21cd-4472-ab66-8edab07856c7", "value": "Solid masonry placed to counteract the lateral thrust of a vault or arch."}
{"id": "2ac16c77-fa9c-435f-9b8e-6585c7c91782", "value": "In the Classical Orders, the horizontal assembly of architrave, frieze and cornice carried upon columns and pilasters."}
{"id": "e6ce7d78-3dec-4539-974e-4135aa62db91", "value": "A vertical, circular member, usually load-carrying. Where separate, use monument type."}

{"id": "e0675055-8858-4c87-80ae-c8f6a6266977", "value": "A series of flat-topped structures, usually wooden or stone, on which a person places their feet when ascending or descending, facilitating movement from one level to another."}
{"id": "ad588d8f-ec11-4e13-b324-57adcf6e7b92", "value": "A covered walkway attached to a building."}
{"id": "50863bab-733e-4f59-97dc-f8d9551bed4d", "value": "A vertical piece of wood fixed on corners of walls to help the fixing of plaster and to protect against damage to the plaster."}

{"id": "bc5607ef-bb7a-43f8-b06f-3b5cb5e6e1ac", "value": "A defined portion of a surface, often a wall lining or door, usually rectangular, which may be recessed, level with or proud of its surrounding surface and may be framed by mouldings or channels."}
{"id": "df552863-8123-4c42-b81f-c740d03efe81", "value": "A stone block set into a wall to support a truss or beam."}
{"id": "d0e650da-2a44-4e41-a2a0-41c92abcefac", "value": "A structure, part of a structure or area constructed from plain bricks."}
{"id": "753a321a-2f9b-4d5b-a6a1-e98a6ff13c9c", "value": "A thin masonry facing or cladding employed to conceal the surface or structure behind it."}
{"id": "3a13f051-8a2b-4aa1-a7b3-7b5e70803ebd", "value": "A vertical member standing without support."}
{"id": "94a21034-56d3-430e-bae6-2680f7d7e699", "value": "The under surface of an arch, lintel or projecting architectural feature."}

{"id": "802f484a-3e37-4bfb-bfe4-4b1275e6c43f", "value": "A projecting structure in the roof of a mill containing a winch, allowing loads to be lifted clear of the building's wall and protecting the winch from the weather."}
{"id": "cd90cb8a-4f2f-4401-a334-2c9afc0d6d3b", "value": "An inclined member used to support laths under a roof covering. Normally one of a pair."}

{"id": "531b57b8-f7fb-4244-9b26-fc50a54ff89b", "value": "A device, usually wooden, or fabric on a timber frame, designed to catch, and be driven by, the wind in order to power a windmill. For maritime uses see the Thesaurus of Maritime Archaeology."}
{"id": "9f09c1c4-7cc1-446c-9715-bf8cffda98cd", "value": "The exterior upper covering, and its supporting structure, of a building."}

{"id": "64d8f120-1ac4-47ed-bee1-1cb06c600049", "value": "A large shallow pan, usually metal, in which seawater or brine is evaporated for the extraction of salt. The name is also often applied to the exterior pits or ponds used for the same purpose (see Thesaurus of Monument Types)."}
{"id": "448e2574-6503-4f97-983e-401cba844e05", "value": "A projecting part of a building that overhangs the wall below it."}
{"id": "28632772-1ae1-4361-8605-7d2272b27c66", "value": "A short timber connecting a cruck blade to a wall above the point at which the blade diverges from it."}
{"id": "cad0dcc1-7dad-4507-b16f-a5312e8d4898", "value": "A strategically placed aperture in the wall of a fortification through which guns and cannon can fire upon an invading force."}
{"id": "d89061cb-24aa-45a2-acea-c7952b934ffd", "value": "An ornamental bracket on either side of a doorway supporting a cornice."}
{"id": "1639f96e-c9ad-484d-939d-db247954bbb5", "value": "An aperture cut obliquely in a wall, usually of a chancel, affording a view between the high altar and the aisles or side chapels."}

{"id": "ae102b56-8d2e-421d-90d9-0e4162dbef14", "value": "A screen, with a wide central opening, or multiple narrower openings, spanning the lower end of a medieval hall, screening the cross entry and defining the screen, or cross, passage."}
{"id": "3bc0ad9c-9234-432f-968d-01646b968220", "value": "A channel or pipeline that feeds water to a waterwheel."}
{"id": "d51e7964-aa70-4b60-b463-24383628f4d0", "value": "A concave groove or series of grooves."}
{"id": "2350f3a2-4289-4574-a30d-32d466de0848", "value": "A projection left on a stone block to allow it to be hoisted into position."}
{"id": "945b287c-7998-4ef0-b775-8a1bf89d2708", "value": "A short timber laid across the top of a masonry wall to carry a wall plate or the foot of a common rafter."}
{"id": "1fea9c4b-7fb9-49b1-9e3a-69edf29e8d03", "value": "A frame to a structure formed by precast concrete beams placed in pairs."}
{"id": "6e25c426-8c92-401f-8a3f-acfaa867f927", "value": "A vertical partition used to separate one area from another."}
{"id": "96627a67-adaf-483a-bca5-9882709c21c3", "value": "A pier made up of several shafts against it. The shafts can be attached or detached."}
{"id": "ef478f01-8c5f-4d4e-9332-7adbf8558be1", "value": "A horizontal member spanning an opening and providing support to the wall above the opening."}
{"id": "f6427f80-2fd6-4d8b-81a3-f08a38e761fe", "value": "A chamber usually used for sleeping."}
{"id": "67fb4c97-103b-4cc9-9289-e4c0c2267599", "value": "A gate or valve that controls the flow of water from a reservoir, harbour, etc.."}
{"id": "1ad2e80d-3be5-49f1-b122-dd606aa200cc", "value": "A small piece of timber occupying the angle between two other timbers."}

{"id": "2febf7ab-c9fc-4faa-a4f2-daf54522bf02", "value": "A mechanism, either automated or consisting of winches and pulleys, that raises sacks of grain on ropes or chains from one floor of a mill to another, usually through one or a series of trap doors."}

{"id": "baa7f6e9-5db0-46f9-a129-8a9db8cb488b", "value": "A large vertical stone forming part of a structure. If the structure is roofed, the orthostat will stretch from the floor to the roof as a single slab."}
{"id": "3f633488-232e-496b-b0b5-e20a6d8fe3bd", "value": "A timber frame placed in the bell chamber of a church tower or belfry designed to hold the bells."}
{"id": "a81a3aa8-f882-4b2a-aa84-3dca41f59c04", "value": "A triangular piece of wood used to raise slates next to a wall or similar."}
{"id": "496cedfc-fb02-4414-a316-cda7c30fde14", "value": "A duct or channel for hot air to travel through."}
{"id": "fd5a76b4-452a-48ad-990f-bf35dc0b905c", "value": "A horizontal timber set in the plane of a roof's slope and supporting common rafters."}
{"id": "86352092-c986-42f1-8317-86a5cd32ccc5", "value": "A tall, circular, polygonal or square structure rising from a roof, tower, turret etc., tapering to a slender point."}

{"id": "620a3a19-b1d7-49af-932b-0160021de549", "value": "The smallest piece of timber (2-5cms) across used in building, employed on rafters to support the roof covering or in a partition as a base for plaster or external render and wall covering."}
{"id": "ea13a01d-0a4d-4cbb-8e43-d7baa6d0ebdc", "value": "A projecting wall or structure, such as a parapet or battlement, supported by a series of corbels."}
{"id": "a9e0d7bc-c199-4583-b763-5b13cdddce03", "value": "A piece of cladding in the form of a length of timber fixed horizontally to the building."}
{"id": "4e60ae94-9649-4d38-8a4a-b0f4a1ffd774", "value": "An inclined wooden trough which channels grain evenly from the feed hopper into the eye of the stones in a corn mill."}
{"id": "22bc523a-b1a4-4772-8071-90c74cd32a19", "value": "A timber set on the back of a cruck blade to carry a purlin."}
{"id": "0815be63-8109-4c63-9c8a-4ef7ae4b766f", "value": "A mass of stone or brick built against or as part of a wall to provide additional strength to it."}
{"id": "30c70a76-1b92-4a3e-8127-a3ac24daf4b2", "value": "The part of the wall that supports a pitched roof at the end of the roof."}
{"id": "ffea714c-71ed-4376-bf7f-b0a22ed737a7", "value": "A series of arches."}
{"id": "2e4c47ed-159b-4f98-b31d-e2c608539208", "value": "A section of a window between mullions; thus for example a three-light window."}
{"id": "d52cf0a6-3e29-4f0d-9070-9dfb880a750c", "value": "A triangular gable usually above an entablature."}
{"id": "8ca45d19-eabf-44dc-a933-3c308911b7e4", "value": "A pad on which a post rests to support part of a structure."}
{"id": "9e13afc7-8ee6-4d4c-bc30-3e83287c795d", "value": "The surface of a room which conceals overhead structural members."}

{"id": "0cb7f783-f0d4-418d-8086-89f0c4715548", "value": "A small tank or cistern, often lead or cast-iron and sometimes ornamented, that collects rainwater from a gutter or channel prior to it being discharged."}
{"id": "0501f854-0f03-4c55-b4ac-ae1867360473", "value": "A thin wooden slab or tile used in quantity as a roof or wall covering."}
{"id": "18532c21-2fbc-4aa9-96f9-3ad8f1e3d9c7", "value": "A structure, usually of brick, stone or timber, that encloses or defines a space or room."}
{"id": "1b7d174d-d96b-4386-905a-55ae78567b2c", "value": "The wedge shaped end of a bridge pier designed to break the current of water."}
{"id": "5ea0e696-5eb5-48b7-83be-31a4f39f5898", "value": "A short timber set on top of two cruck blades."}

{"id": "3562798c-dddf-4476-825e-8cba79c69544", "value": "Any structural component, usually of wood, which is believed to have derived from a vessel. Double index with the appropriate type of structural component eg. BEAM or if known the original term from the MARITIME FIXTURES AND FITTINGS thesaurus."}
{"id": "6558b3c5-5c26-4c29-af8d-ea1e41d37c02", "value": "A main load-bearing horizontal member."}

{"id": "28e3decf-6ec2-44fe-8761-7ef811f5de16", "value": "A triangular or wedge-shaped timber cocking-piece attached to the upper face of a rafter near its foot in order to reduce the slope above the eaves. Such eaves are referred to as being sprocketed."}
{"id": "121d4256-138e-49d2-a45f-6b31eac1c1c4", "value": "The main vertical axle running through the centre of a mill."}
{"id": "da7a41b9-fc39-47fd-ada4-e3b1bbd937ad", "value": "Timber framed construction where a box of horizontal and vertical members is created to support the roof."}
{"id": "87413285-1f5c-4eae-ab71-8331facc1d9c", "value": "Glass that has been coloured by fusing glass with a metallic oxide film or by burning pigment into the surface."}

{"id": "3f1fe3bc-40fd-4f14-9c41-dfb365ae48bf", "value": "An adjustable, horizontal beam, supporting the vertical stone spindle in a water or windmill, which allows the gap between the grinding stones to be varied."}
{"id": "19da2615-d222-4f40-bbe6-39665a153dd3", "value": "The hole through which the fuel for a fire is put to start and maintain the fire."}
{"id": "6283174b-54bc-420d-8d55-685f4dac06d7", "value": "A sloping timber in a staircase holding the ends of treads and risers."}
{"id": "ecd87eee-933e-459b-a14d-e45d88f4f5b2", "value": "A diagonal or arched member placed across rafters to stiffen and support a roof structure."}
{"id": "36fed28a-bcbb-43f5-ae8b-cf78f24bca3d", "value": "The corner upright bar of a polygonal sash."}
{"id": "6320fc7a-31ce-4f0e-9a8e-ad820e69815d", "value": "An upright framing member, or mullion, that separates two panels, such as in a panelled door or a window."}
{"id": "cd6cbcab-a4bc-44d6-b20f-12fcc5c12960", "value": "A base on which a statue, column etc. stands."}
{"id": "2d0ae2d4-470e-4188-95d5-f27a1bdceb38", "value": "A recess within a wall or room."}

{"id": "08ec34bb-c140-45b7-b438-acf3fe62d712", "value": "The horizontal piece of timber or stone forming the bottom of a window, doorway or other opening, usually and properly designed to throw off water."}
{"id": "5d5241a0-aa82-4ddf-abcd-4f238f3eb404", "value": "A stone edging on a footway dividing it from a carriageway."}
{"id": "bb496058-07b6-4eb0-a8fd-ff602ae14f42", "value": "A trough or watercourse constructed to collect rainwater from a roof and channel it towards a drain or pipe."}
{"id": "5e668b78-cde9-492f-94ca-42c0d0fc2257", "value": "An inclined course on top of a projecting sill, cornice etc., designed to throw off rainwater."}
{"id": "c99b5ac8-c392-4e3a-9b7a-99ba48b77936", "value": "A row of columns that carry arches or an entablature."}
{"id": "b1f4a628-3b69-4850-862c-ecc8cd865977", "value": "An iron plate connecting two or more timbers together."}
{"id": "44bbb44f-9a12-46a9-a9aa-0f04c6733015", "value": "A small square or lozenge-shaped pane of glass as used in a leaded light."}
{"id": "f063a901-c26c-4cc6-b631-e0239e1f496a", "value": "A timber placed horizontally in a cob or stone wall to support the foot of a post or cruck blade."}
{"id": "3f86faa7-f70d-432b-b360-24a423e3009d", "value": "A carved, convex block, often richly decorated, at the intersections of vault-ribs, beam-junctions or terminations of mouldings."}
{"id": "3da1b37c-6bbc-4cad-b140-df4b13b0ecba", "value": "A structural member that supports a purlin. Use PRINCIPAL RAFTER where the principal is also a common rafter."}
{"id": "29a180c9-ff37-4485-b6d8-1fed4a962c10", "value": "A horizontal timber positioned at the bottom of a framed wall into which posts and studs are tenoned."}

{"id": "eadf3b0a-7dfa-4789-bfd3-da0632e18f43", "value": "The gearwheel on the upright shaft within a windmill from which secondary drives operating other parts of the machinery are powered. are taken"}
{"id": "11269971-5ea6-4d74-997b-386cfc7f1488", "value": "A horizontal member dividing a window into two or more lights."}
{"id": "c31dfb6b-2c3e-42de-8d5b-d6832d9046e7", "value": "A wedge shaped stone or brick forming part of an arch or vault, with its radiating sides coinciding with the radii of that arch."}
{"id": "462ca222-b00d-433e-b346-2f429fb33c5f", "value": "A narrow timber board or moulding lining the base of an interior wall as a finish between it and and the floor."}
{"id": "aa3c6003-9b46-4bf5-906c-1c10acfa8f64", "value": "A vertical member dividing a window into two or more lights."}
{"id": "131fa38e-447f-40d3-80fa-3e625c985046", "value": "A stone, usually inscribed, laid during a ceremony to commemorate the founding of a new building"}
{"id": "4a44424d-869b-44b5-86c1-8af5e37ef776", "value": "A float or pontoon supporting a flexible steel roadway as part of a Mulberry Harbour."}
{"id": "f5bf99a5-0797-4338-89b8-06bef5c16ae3", "value": "A glazed opening in a roof or ceiling."}
{"id": "941277a8-ecd4-4804-b52d-b354d0e62ee4", "value": "A housing for one or more bells, usually gabled or roofed."}
{"id": "9e8e3b98-6f3e-4080-b072-7302186e100d", "value": "A solid support of masonry to sustain vertical pressure and frequently each of the pillars from which an arch springs."}

{"id": "4bab3622-37ad-4562-a510-ab5c5ed3af72", "value": "The face within a pediment, as enclosed by the cornices, or the solid infill of an arch above an impost, sometimes embellished with sculptural or relief ornament."}
{"id": "7dc74046-a09d-41b4-81e2-12a801893914", "value": "The top stone in a gable end."}

{"id": "f2f274ad-5203-44a4-b159-d7713693b832", "value": "The structure consisting of a series of balusters supporting a rail or coping, and sometimes a base and pedestal, on a parapet, balcony or staircase."}
{"id": "df6fc54c-fa71-45ba-bc26-7d7ce2cbb64a", "value": "A part of an arch between the apex and the springer."}
{"id": "5c50270c-d9f7-4dbc-af10-dbb430c45e0c", "value": "A gap which allows air to circulate."}
{"id": "18720f52-c52d-4b07-9677-a09b8d5c15f1", "value": "Pinion which engages with the spur wheel and drives the millstones in a corn mill."}
{"id": "35642f6c-7f2b-4bf9-97e6-677bdc51dd9b", "value": "A funnel-like container from which grain or other material is fed to a grinding mechanism below."}

{"id": "9e2d481d-2f81-473b-873a-c894fe360c37", "value": "A small auxiliary engine to help start up a large steam engine - invented 1866."}

{"id": "0925f073-4c4f-45ef-82c5-9b3d9a8d2fa1", "value": "A piece of machinery used to convert energy of one sort (for instance steam) into motive energy."}

{"id": "ccb72e97-9d03-4d43-b647-df96982f8ba7", "value": "An early design of pump featuring a series of pistons, or sometimes bundles of rags, passing through a barrel on a continuous chain, forcing water upwards."}
{"id": "eebadfb6-b4eb-4689-a1a1-711b75f1d6c0", "value": "A pump for removing condensed steam from the condenser of a steam raising plant."}

{"id": "a32eef29-1354-413a-bc6e-580474b6cf9b", "value": "The lowest of the three main parts of an entablature. Also the lintels, jambs and mouldings surrounding a door, window, panels or niche; or the ornamental mouldings around the exterior curve of an arch."}

{"id": "7974e425-49af-4513-a361-c5d8ab6e7a94", "value": "A decorative structure of wood stone or metal, incorporating a shelf, surrounding the opening of a fireplace."}

{"id": "6488f2e0-046d-4210-829d-37e245abc56f", "value": "A classical order with an Attic base and fluted column. The cornice has dentils and the capital volutes."}

{"id": "bca43d3e-764e-47bb-b3e2-541ff8b18ec8", "value": "A joint in which the dovetailed member is proud of the receiving member and is not finished flush with it."}
{"id": "0f7358f6-2a9e-4ffb-8502-997f63b9743d", "value": "A joint in which the end is shaped like a dovetail."}
{"id": "4c04c86d-73fa-4095-a81c-c4cb94275dfb", "value": "A communal sleeping room in medieval houses for male servants."}

{"id": "085c448d-533f-4ed3-98f9-6a0e089461bb", "value": "An arcaded upper aisle, wall passage or blind arcade, usually occurring in large Romanesque or Gothic churches, above the aisle and below the clerestory."}

{"id": "b2784128-dacf-4720-9b80-5eb02d3c6f83", "value": "A design of steam engine in which either three cylinders, in the case of vertical engines, or four cylinders on horizontal engines, permit steam to be expanded three times as it passes through the installation."}
{"id": "aaa9d033-eace-46a9-9cef-48edc82a146f", "value": "An ornamental panel or decorative structure situated above a mantelpiece"}

{"id": "c0437716-75c3-44f5-929d-feb73004c1c0", "value": "A decorative feature, or non-heraldic badge, representing the name of a person connected with a building, often in the form of a graphic pun on the name."}
{"id": "c9e3d4da-b1e1-40a5-99a9-c711ee306c23", "value": "A component part that is designed deliberately for decorative purposes."}
{"id": "5dbd058a-4314-4b12-b102-066497cbc14d", "value": "A flat oval or circular ornamental feature decorated in relief, often with flutes or floral motifs."}
{"id": "87534e8a-d481-4cbc-9ecd-1b69a42aee50", "value": "A decorative feature, usually Norman, in which fluting takes a spiral rather than vertical form."}

{"id": "d6ebfb40-a4b0-4495-ba55-de94d00b9a30", "value": "Small 'drops' or conic projections under the mutules (a repeating block motif) and triglyphs (rectangular blocks embellished with vertical grooves) in a Doric entablature."}
{"id": "c735955b-e47e-47c6-8b4e-d4a342f8d99b", "value": "Decorative ornamentation in the form of a horn filled with fruit etc."}
{"id": "008bca08-aebc-4eac-a729-df2be7a3be5d", "value": "The shaped projection on the top of a newel post or at the apex of a gable."}
{"id": "fce567b3-7eb1-4400-8c15-3f6af1fa9760", "value": "A case or border, usually wood or metal, enclosing a picture, painting or photograph."}

{"id": "e1cc5f4d-5d68-4dc2-822c-1ae6f96ba4bf", "value": "An arrangement by which panels, screens, vaults or windows are divided into parts of different shapes or sizes by means of moulded stone bars or ribs, called form-pieces or forms in the Medieval period."}

{"id": "47365cc7-081e-4fda-94e4-fc0aedb9f79d", "value": "Paper, often decorated with a printed pattern, painted or embossed design, and usually provided in rolls and used to line the interior walls of a building for decorative purposes."}

{"id": "25664af2-87f3-4cb9-98bc-00db03414ff9", "value": "A display or depiction of authorised armorial bearings, such as the elements of a coat of arms, livery and personal badges and flags, mottoes etc.."}
{"id": "76f4abc5-fdae-47d9-b887-37f3eed7e354", "value": "An oval or circular decorative feature often bearing an illustration or portrait in light relief."}
{"id": "28f77f36-d08b-429e-ad25-f5821a13a2ff", "value": "Fine art depiction in oil, watercolour or other media on wood panels, canvas or paper"}
{"id": "0d97fbf9-921a-4c3d-8e58-6a5e6a87e1ec", "value": "A two dimensional image using paint applied to the surface of a wall."}

{"id": "82f4c906-4bb8-4d28-82c4-7c19ef5ee62d", "value": "A decorative feature of wood, plaster or carved masonry, often used in low relief on ceilings, panels or screens and resembling interlacing leather straps. Popular in the late 16th and early 17th centuries."}
{"id": "68d274ab-d250-4bc9-bf46-47fbfa6c3612", "value": "A surface formed by cutting off a square edge, usually at 45 degrees. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "3398a536-ba85-41ab-9abf-3a32a48d7ee7", "value": "A series of panels, usually of wood, combined to line a room."}
{"id": "61c1b969-ac34-4523-9667-8879a0fce98e", "value": "Circular or almond-shaped halo surrounding the figure of Christ, the Virgin or a saint."}
{"id": "3688882d-da36-4ff4-afc6-0d407f9f683e", "value": "A sculptural or decorative representation of a human figure. Includes mythical and fantastical figures such as Cupid, Atlas etc."}

{"id": "a72e45ac-c4fb-4d2f-aa3b-0dd7efc1b365", "value": "The application of colour and other materials to a structure to either conceal it from identification or to make it look like something else."}
{"id": "c96e8bd7-2723-4d24-ae06-68c6a511e503", "value": "An inscription on illustration applied to a wall by carving into its plaster to reveal a different colour beneath."}
{"id": "e45ff8c3-8aa3-4e94-80c3-5e567fae921b", "value": "A decorative, framed tablet, usually bearing an inscription or coat of arms, in the form of a scroll or curving piece of parchment."}

{"id": "f89fed67-45b9-469c-94cc-4e0ce987f5cc", "value": "A sculptural or decorative representation of an animal. Includes mythical and fantastical animals such as dragons, centaurs etc."}
{"id": "0e3e6491-7211-4cae-8181-7fefa5be4e7d", "value": "A decorative tile on the end of the cornice or eaves of a building to conceal the ends of tiles."}
{"id": "65a83773-1879-4089-9816-83096c732b8d", "value": "Decorative ornamentation in the form of interlacing ribbons or cords, usually in an intricate pattern."}
{"id": "82693b51-137c-45dd-9b34-f562bd1be447", "value": "Decorative ornamentation consisting of alternating oval and V-shaped motifs, used to enrich ovolo mouldings."}
